# Tariff - Global Trade Simulation Game

## Overview
Tariff is an interactive 3D visualization game that simulates global trade dynamics using Three.js. Players can observe and manipulate trade parameters to achieve global economic equilibrium through tariff adjustments.

## Core Game Mechanics

### Visual Representation
- 3D globe using Three.js with country borders highlighted
- Dynamic trade routes visualized as flowing lines between countries
- Color-coded indicators for:
  - Trade surplus (green)
  - Trade deficit (red)
  - Balanced trade (blue)
- Real-time GDP growth/decline visualization through country size/glow effects

### Simulation Parameters
1. **Tariff Rates**
   - Range: 0% to 100%
   - Affects import/export volumes
   - Visual impact on trade route thickness

2. **GDP Indicators**
   - Per country GDP growth/decline
   - Visual representation through country size/glow
   - Historical GDP trends graph

3. **Trade Metrics**
   - Import volumes
   - Export volumes
   - Trade balance
   - Bilateral trade relationships

4. **Additional Parameters**
   - Currency exchange rates
   - Population growth
   - Industrial production index
   - Consumer confidence index

### Game Controls
- Play/Pause button
- Reset button
- Speed control (0.5x to 2x)
- Parameter adjustment sliders
- Country selection for detailed view

### Game Flow
1. **Initialization (5 seconds)**
   - Load world map
   - Initialize trade routes
   - Set initial parameters

2. **Main Simulation (45 seconds)**
   - Real-time parameter updates
   - Dynamic trade route visualization
   - Economic indicator updates

3. **End Game (10 seconds)**
   - Victory screen when all trade balances are equal
   - Final statistics display
   - Option to restart

## Technical Requirements

### Frontend
- Three.js for 3D visualization
- React for UI components
- D3.js for data visualization
- WebGL for performance optimization

### Data Structure
```typescript
interface Country {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  gdp: number;
  population: number;
  coordinates: {
    lat: number;
    lng: number;
  };
  tradePartners: TradePartner[];
}

interface TradePartner {
  countryId: string;
  importVolume: number;
  exportVolume: number;
  tariffRate: number;
}

interface GameState {
  isRunning: boolean;
  currentTime: number;
  countries: Country[];
  globalParameters: GlobalParameters;
}

interface GlobalParameters {
  baseTariffRate: number;
  gdpGrowthRate: number;
  tradeMultiplier: number;
}
```

### Performance Targets
- 60 FPS minimum
- Less than 100ms initial load time
- Less than 16ms per frame update time

## Victory Conditions
- All countries achieve trade balance within 1% margin
- No country experiences > 5% GDP decline
- Global trade volume remains stable

